  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Integrated AI will lead to paradigm shifts in EWS.",
    "First, AI, especially Meteorological FMs, are already revolutionizing weather and hazard forecasts, leading to enormous improvements in lead times and resolution of warnings before disaster strikes.",
    "Second, multi-modal AI, materialized through Impact FMs, can leverage geospatial and socio-economic data to assess vulnerabilities and tear down previously existing silos impeding effective impact-based warnings.",
    "Third, multihazard EWS, soon being implemented across the globe for the UN EarlyWarningsForAll initiative, should not miss the opportunities of multi-modal AI, circumventing the rigidity of existing systems, and incorporating the whole early warning chain, including communication, into an Early Warning FM that allows users a ChatBot-like interactive experience with warnings.",
    "Finally, causal machine learning, once mature, will enable interpretable analysis of the Early Warning FM and lead to more effective decision making, as the effects of interventions can be predicted through What-If scenarios."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}